Algemene teort aan privaat finansiering vir groter projekte

We are currently experiencing long delays with most projects that are going through State approval processes.
This means that for us to resource our company to deal with future work we are putting ourselves as great risk. This could mean having to down size and laying from off valuable personnel.

The Zuma factor, weak Rand, Junk status, and low growth are all affecting the appetite for new development while the willingness of corporations to enter into long term leases and a tightening of debt funding thresholds are all affecting the profession which is in many ways a bellweather of the economy.
A significant raise in interest rates will also dampen the residential market which is the one sector at the moment showing some life.
